## (5)(a) ITU 5G Triangle

> Draw and explain the ITU specified triangle of 5G. *(8 marks)*

---

The **ITU IMT-2020** framework defines 5G through three use case categories:

::itu-triangle

---

**1. eMBB (Enhanced Mobile Broadband)**

High-speed data for bandwidth-hungry applications.

- **Peak speed:** 20 Gbps
- **User experienced:** 100 Mbps
- **Use cases:** 4K/8K streaming, VR/AR, cloud gaming

---

**2. URLLC (Ultra-Reliable Low-Latency Communication)**

Mission-critical applications where delay = danger.

- **Latency:** under 1 ms
- **Reliability:** 99.999% (five nines)
- **Use cases:** Remote surgery, autonomous vehicles, industrial robots

---

**3. mMTC (Massive Machine-Type Communication)**

Connecting billions of IoT devices.

- **Density:** 1 million devices per kmÂ²
- **Battery life:** 10+ years
- **Use cases:** Smart meters, agriculture sensors, asset tracking

---

| Use Case | Speed | Latency | Devices | Key Metric |
|----------|-------|---------|---------|------------|
| **eMBB** | 20 Gbps | ~10 ms | Few | Throughput |
| **URLLC** | Medium | 1 ms | Few | Reliability |
| **mMTC** | Low | Relaxed | Millions | Density |

